<br>
First off I have the lvl 60 pet heal (which is key to my strat) and I also have the epic. Boots of bladecalling are nice to have if not just mem a low level nuke.<br>
<br>
1 summon pet at the entrance close to the zone out and park him there. Give him muzzle and bo4. <br>
<br>
2 pull a centi with malosini. On the way back hit pet attack as you can be almost anywhere in the zone and your pet will respond, but won't attack until you get him into range. Run back to your pet staying in the middle and stop before you hit the wall. If you go all the way to the wall the mob is likely to run backwards in order to find a path to you, as this place is a bit buggy on pathing.<br>
<br>
3 pet will aggro the mob before it gets to you and stop him. either cast your low level nuke or hit boots to do some damage. Then sit and just cast 52/60 pet heal as needed. Once the battle is over make sure your pet is at least 80+ on life. Go pull another mob and repeat. Your epic pet with constant chain healing can take 2 regular centi's at once but you must have full mana before doing this. Toss in a rain spell to hit both mobs around half way thru the fight to do some damage.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Pulling tips<br>
<br>
There are around 3-4 roaming transient centi's that will path down the hall towards the zone go almost to the wall then turn around and path back. Need to watch for them while fighting. But if you see one coming while the one you are on is almost dead don't worry it should be no problem to kill him also.<br>
<br>
At the end of the first hall there are 3 static spawn points.<br>
One up before the broken pieces on the floor, and 2 on either side of the hall right before the steps. Each of these can be pulled solo just watch out for transients as they will aggro if close.<br>
<br>
Next pull after these 3 is down the steps and to the right. Behind the broken pillar to your right is a single static spawn. Easy solo pull.<br>
<br>
Next pull is the two on the east hall steps. This pull is tricky sometimes I have soloed and sometimes its a double. Not sure on why. So make sure you are close to fm before trying and always expect to pull both.<br>
<br>
Next pull you have a choice. There will be wandering centis from the north hall to the east hall that you can pick off, or wandering centis from the east to south hall. Pick off these if you see them.<br>
<br>
Now the big choice. Going north there are 2 centi(blue a bit harder then the black) these guys are linked in my experience. If you manage to pull one both will come. They like to hide inside the walls so you can't see them.<br>
<br>
Pulling from the north hall is tricky as they mobs from there don't like to path down the stairs and you can run into traps. So its better to continue to pull from the east hall.<br>
<br>
In the east hall its basically one mob in middle just past the stairs. One mob on left up behind the first mob. One mob on the right towards the end of the hall. And finally one mob (usually a sk as he seems to harm touch) towards the end on the left. All of these are solo pulls.<br>
<br>
Its hard to get to the end of the east hall before repops so make sure you watch out for them and repull as they pop.<br>
This way I can (if i have kei) pull non stop until kei wears off. Or pull around 7-8 before having to med at all.<br>
<br>
So thats my little guide to Akheva.<br>
<br>
Few things also if you get a train announce it if others are in the zone and make sure to take the train out the side where people are not at.<br>
<br>
Do not train mobs to akheva zone in from maidens. The 4arms in maidens will get stuck at the zone and will not path home. I personally have had 2 gm rezes from this bug. The 4 arms are instant death if you zone into them as they like to harm touch, espically if you are zoning on low hp. If this happens to you petition and get a gm there to look at it and explain they were trapped at the zone. You will get a rez and maybe someday the pathing there will get fixed. <p><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=172682"> Cullyn </A><br>
